{"actual_usd":0.126045,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":242,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24483,"reply":"\"No, I don't think it fizzled.\" *I hook a flour-dusted thumb into the edge of my apron and glance toward the bright patch of floor by the bakery door, thinking how bread can be done in one sense and still need time to rise before anybody eats it.* \"I think it was the actual thing, more or less. The sort of victory that changes what time we're living in before it changes every last thing you can point at with your finger.\"\n\n*I twirl that gray-streaked strand once, slow.* \"Like yeast worked through dough, maybe. The life is really in there already. But the loaf isn't baked yet, and pretending it is would be foolish; saying nothing happened would be foolish too.\"\n\n\"The resurrection feels to me like the kingdom broke in for real—decisive, not symbolic—and now we're in the strange middle where death's been beaten without having quit its noise.\" *I lift one shoulder.* \"So no, not a rehearsal. More like the first true morning, and we're still living by its light before noon has come.\"\n\n\"What part catches in you most—the waiting, or the not-yet-looking-so-much-like victory?\"","rolling_24h_usd":78.43943499999997,"run_id":"829342d6-82e3-4e85-99d8-851689b2781d"}
